        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20686\">#20686</a> adds a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=CompletableTopField#doc\">docs#CompletableTopField</a> instance for a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=NormedField#doc\">docs#NormedField</a> and could do with a review (it's been sitting idle for almost a month).</p>\n<p>I would think the instance is non-controversial. There may be a slicker proof for the <code>nice</code> field (which I do by going back to epsilons and deltas), but I would think it should be fine unless (and until) someone comes up with a better proof.</p>\n<p>See also the Zulip messages around <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Gelfand-Mazur.20theorem/near/493194350\">this one</a>.</p>",
